usage run the below scripts in order:
month.py, month2.py, month3.py
They all generate some csv file.

To see csv file nicely run beautify.py

To plot csv file as candlelight chart use bar.py

To genreate report for a ticker use report.py


==================Example Run for analyzing SPY history from 2007 to 2026 ==================
  Step 1 — Fetch data (required)

  python3 month.py -t SPY -s 2007-01-01 -e 2026-01-01 -i monthly
  # Output: spy_monthly_candles_2007_2026.csv

  Step 2 — Merge same-color candles (required)

  python3 month2.py -i spy_monthly_candles_2007_2026.csv
  # Output: spy_monthly_candles_2007_2026_merged.csv

  Step 3 — Merge by threshold (optional)
  Absorbs small counter-trend candles into the dominant trend. Tune the % threshold to your taste (e.g. 6 means ignore reversals under 6%).

  python3 month3.py -i spy_monthly_candles_2007_2026_merged.csv -t 6
  # Output: spy_monthly_candles_2007_2026_merged_merged_v2.csv

  ---
  Visualization / Output — pick any or all (all optional)

  Interactive chart (recommended):
  python3 bar.py spy_monthly_candles_2007_2026_merged_merged_v2.csv
  # or with v2:
  python script/bar.py spy_monthly_candles_2007_2026_merged_merged_v2.csv
  # Output: opens an HTML chart in browser

  Statistical report:
  python3 report.py spy_monthly_candles_2007_2026_merged_merged_v2.csv
  # Output: spy_monthly_candles_2007_2026_merged.report

  Human-readable text table:
  python3 beautify.py spy_monthly_candles_2007_2026_merged_merged_v2.csv spy_trends.txt
  # Output: spy_trends.txt
